Class ProjectList

java.lang.Object
models.ProjectList
public class ProjectList extends Object
This class is one that contains a list of project in the fyp management system. It stores all the information of all projects.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Dennis Chen

      public static List<Project> getUserSpecificProjectList(String userName)
      This method gets all the project in the list of project that have the username in the project object, be it be the project's supervisor. It will run through all the project and append it into a new list of project.

      Returns:

    • getStatusSpecificProjectList

      public static List<Project> getStatusSpecificProjectList(ProjectStatus status)
      This method gets all the project in the list of project that have this particular project status in the project object. It will run through all the project and append it into a new list of projects.
      Parameters:
      status - this is the specific project status that wants to get back in all project
      Returns:
      the list of project with this particular status.

    • getSpecificProject

      public static Project getSpecificProject(int projectID)
      Thie methods get the project that is in this class project list based on what is the project id inputted. If such a project id is not found in the project list, it will get nothing.
      Parameters:
      projectID - This is the value of the project id that you want to get back.
      Returns:
      the project object of the specificed project id.

    • getSpecificAvailableProject

      public static Project getSpecificAvailableProject(int projectID)
      Thie methods get the available project that is in this class project list based on what is the project id inputted. If such a project id is not found in the project list, it will get nothing. If such a project id is found but the status is not available, it will get nothing
      Parameters:
      projectID - This is the value of the project id that you want to get back.
      Returns:
      the available status project object of the specificed project id.
